    <note type="biography">
        <p>Gardener to the Warner family at Hoddeston. Partner with Robert Parker in a nursery at Seven Sisters Road, Holloway, London, 1854–61; subsequently moved to Victoria and Paradise Nurseries, Upper Holloway. A specialist on orchids, he was the author of the popular work <hi rend="italic">The orchid grower’s manual</hi> (1852), which was the first successful manual giving instructions for the cultivation of orchids.</p></note>
    <note type="sources">
        <p>R. Desmond 1977, Reinikka 1972, Stewart ed. 1992.</p>
